===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|indolentem|lang=la}} from {{term|in-||not|lang=la}} + {{term|dolens|dolēns|pain|lang=la}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK|US}} {{IPA|/ˈɪn.dəl.ənt/}}, {{SAMPA|/'Ind@l@nt/}}
* {{audio|en-us-indolent.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# [[habitually|Habitually]] [[lazy]], [[procrastinate|procrastinating]], or resistant to physical labor/labour.
#: ''The '''indolent''' girl resisted doing her homework.''
# [[induce|Inducing]] [[laziness]] (e.g. '''''indolent''' comfort'').
# {{medicine}} Causing [[scant]] or no physical pain; progressing slowly; inactive (of an [[ulcer]], etc.).
# {{medicine}} Healing slowly.

